The paper deals with the problem of compressed sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of non-convex penalty functions and optimization algorithms, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also presents numerical experiments involving image processing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical properties of the penalty function and optimization algorithm, which could be relevant to optimization and statistics (cs.SI).
